Target: An ontology developed for representing potential energy surface scans.

Comment: A scan of potential energy surface on a molecular system along defined scan coordinates.
Label: PESScan

Comment: A single point on potential energy surface.
The atoms defining a path along the potential energy surface.
Two atoms defining a distance coordinate along the potential energy surface.
Three atoms defining an angle coordinate along the potential energy surface.
Four atoms defining a dihedral angle coordinate along the potential energy surface.
Value of an actual scan coordinate at a given point on a potential energy surface.
Defines the relationship between the PESScan and species in OntoSpecies.
Defines the relationship between the PESScan and a fragment that is a species in OntoSpecies.
Defines the relationship between the PESScan and ScanCoordinate.
Defines the relationship between the ScanCoordinate and ScanPoint .
Defines the relationship between the ScanPoint and ScanCoordinateValue.
Defines the relationship between the ScanCoordinate and an atom.
Defines a relationship between a given ScanPoint and associated calculation results.
Defines a relationship between a given ScanPoint and the atom IDs in the input file used for the scan.
